    "description": {
      "value": "<h2>Standard Racial Traits</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Ability Score Modifiers:</strong> Orang-pendaks are strong and intuitive, but not particularly clever. They gain +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;and +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Wisdom-Wis-\">Wisdom</a>&nbsp;but suffer –2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Size:</strong> Orang-pendaks are Small creatures and gain a +1&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;to their AC, a +1&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>, a –1 penalty on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuvers\">combat maneuver</a>&nbsp;checks and to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuver-Defense\">CMD</a>, and a +4&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Size-Bonus\">size bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;checks.</li>\n<li><strong>Base&nbsp;Speed:</strong> Orang-pendaks have a base speed of 30 feet.</li>\n<li><strong>Languages: </strong>Orang-pendaks begin play speaking Sasquatch. Orang-pendaks who have high&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Intelligence-Int-\">Intelligence</a>&nbsp;scores can choose from the following: Aklo, Common, Draconic, Goblin, Grippli, Sylvan, Vanaran, and Vishkanya. See the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/linguistics\">Linguistics skill page</a>&nbsp;for more information about these languages.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Skill Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Forest Walker (Ex)</strong>&nbsp;Orang-pendaks gain a +4 bonus on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/climb\">Climb</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/stealth\">Stealth</a>&nbsp;checks in forests and jungles.</li>\n<li><strong>Simian Empathy (Ex)&nbsp;</strong>Orang-pendaks gain a +4&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Racial-Bonus\">racial bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/skills/handle-animal\">Handle Animal</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/classes/core-classes/druid#TOC-Wild-Empathy-Ex-\">wild empathy</a>&nbsp;checks with apes and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/bestiary/monster-listings/animals/primates/primate-monkey\">monkeys</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Tear Apart (Ex)</strong>&nbsp;Orang-pendaks have powerful upper bodies and gain a +2&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/glossary#TOC-Racial-Bonus\">racial bonus</a>&nbsp;on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/basics-ability-scores/ability-scores#TOC-Strength-Str-\">Strength</a>&nbsp;checks to break or burst an object. This bonus also applies on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Combat-Maneuvers\">combat maneuver</a>&nbsp;checks to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Sunder\">sunder</a>&nbsp;with their unarmed attacks.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Other Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<h4><strong>Own Two Feet (Ex)</strong>&nbsp;Orang-pendaks are extremely unnerved whenever they are riding another creature or on a vehicle, and they take a – 2 penalty on ability checks,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Attack-Roll\">attack rolls</a>, damage rolls, saving throws, and skill checks when doing so.</h4>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Senses Racial Traits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Low-Light Vision: </strong>Orang-pendaks can see twice as far as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/races/core-races/human\">humans</a>&nbsp;in conditions of dim light.</li>\n</ul>",
